# Universal junk excludes — applied to every service build (web, agent,
# keeperhub, inference). Service-specific tightening lives in
# `<dockerfile-path>.dockerignore` next to each Dockerfile.
#
# Do NOT exclude /web, /agent, /keeperhub, or /tools here — they're build
# contexts for the multi-service docker-compose stack.

.git
.dmux
.claude
node_modules
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/build
**/coverage
**/.cache
**/.venv
**/venv

# Foundry / contracts artifacts (regen via `forge build`)
contracts/cache
contracts/out
contracts/broadcast
contracts/lib

# ML training artifacts (huge; inference image only needs ml/artifacts/merged).
# The negation lets the merged checkpoint ship into the inference build context.
ml/artifacts
!ml/artifacts/merged
!ml/artifacts/merged/**
ml/datasets

# Python caches
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache

# Editor/OS
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store

# Next.js loads .env.local at build time with the highest priority, including
# during `next build`. If we ship web/.env.local into the docker context, its
# `NEXT_PUBLIC_AGENT_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8787` gets inlined into the
# production bundle and the dashboard tries to reach the user's own laptop
# instead of the same-origin /agent mount Caddy proxies.
**/.env.local
**/.env.development.local
**/.env.test.local
